│ derived from operations that effectively work at the element level and may    │
│ need scaling when ScalarTy is a vector-of-scalars (REVEC scenario). The       │
│ instruction emission path handles this scaling (lines ~14292-14299), but the  │
│ cost path does not. Therefore, when ScalarTy has more than one element,       │
│ CommonMask is not transformed, and SubVectorsMask is built at scalar          │
│ granularity, causing the size mismatch and triggering the assertion.\n\n4.    │
│ Proposed Edit Point(s):\nWe need to add the same mask scaling logic to        │
│ ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize as exists in                                   │
│ ShuffleInstructionBuilder::finalize. Specifically:\n- Compute                 │
│ ScalarTyNumElements = getNumElements(ScalarTy).\n- If ScalarTyNumElements !=  │
│ 1, call transformScalarShuffleIndiciesToVector(ScalarTyNumElements,           │
│ CommonMask) and also transform SubVectorsMask similarly, so both masks are at │
│ the same granularity before the size assertion and subsequent operations.\n-  │
│ This should be done at the beginning of ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize,       │
│ before any use of CommonMask/SubVectorsMask and before Action or subvector    │
│ insertion cost computations.\n\nEdit                                          │
│ (llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp:10850-10900):\n- Insert code │
│ to compute ScalarTyNumElements and transform CommonMask and SubVectorsMask    │
│ when ScalarTyNumElements != 1, mirroring the logic in the instruction builder │
│ finalize.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nBy adding the missing mask transformation in     │
│ ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize to handle REVEC cases, we ensure CommonMask    │
│ and SubVectorsMask have consistent sizes and semantics in the cost path,      │
│ matching the emission path behavior. This resolves the assertion failure and  │
│ aligns cost estimation with instruction construction, preventing the SIGABRT  │
│ during opt runs on the provided reproducer."                                  │
│ }                                                                             │
