│                                                                               │
│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash is an assertion failure in BoUpSLP::ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize: │
│ "Expected same size of masks for subvectors and common mask." This indicates  │
│ that, during cost computation for a gather/build-vector with subvector        │
│ insertions, the SubVectorsMask and CommonMask do not have matching sizes.     │
│ Assertions in this area are designed to catch inconsistent mask handling, so  │
│ we should assume the assertion is correct and find where mask sizes diverge.  │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ The SLP pass attempts to vectorize a sequence of compares and their operands. │
│ It builds bundles and eventually reaches the cost calculation for a gather    │
│ involving trunc, or, freeze, etc. The failure occurs while finalizing shuffle │
│ cost estimation. Notably, in ShuffleInstructionBuilder::finalize (the         │
│ emission path), there is logic to transform masks when the scalar element     │
│ type is itself a vector (REVEC case). Specifically, it adjusts CommonMask and │
│ ExtMask to account for the number of elements in ScalarTy                     │
│ (ScalarTyNumElements), via transformScalarShuffleIndiciesToVector. In         │
│ contrast, ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize (the cost path) lacks such           │
│ transformation code. This discrepancy can lead to CommonMask being scaled to  │
│ the element count in one path but not the other, causing size mismatches      │
│ against SubVectorsMask.                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ In the cost estimator finalize (lines ~10850-10931), when SubVectors are      │
│ present, it assumes SubVectorsMask.size() == CommonMask.size(). However,      │
│ CommonMask can be derived from operations that effectively work at the        │
│ element level and may need scaling when ScalarTy is a vector-of-scalars       │
│ (REVEC scenario). The instruction emission path handles this scaling (lines   │
│ ~14292-14299), but the cost path does not. Therefore, when ScalarTy has more  │
│ than one element, CommonMask is not transformed, and SubVectorsMask is built  │
│ at scalar granularity, causing the size mismatch and triggering the           │
│ assertion.                                                                    │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ We need to add the same mask scaling logic to ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize  │
│ as exists in ShuffleInstructionBuilder::finalize. Specifically:               │
│ - Compute ScalarTyNumElements = getNumElements(ScalarTy).                     │
│ - If ScalarTyNumElements != 1, call                                           │
│ transformScalarShuffleIndiciesToVector(ScalarTyNumElements, CommonMask) and   │
│ also transform SubVectorsMask similarly, so both masks are at the same        │
│ granularity before the size assertion and subsequent operations.              │
│ - This should be done at the beginning of ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize,     │
│ before any use of CommonMask/SubVectorsMask and before Action or subvector    │
│ insertion cost computations.                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit (llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp:10850-10900):           │
│ - Insert code to compute ScalarTyNumElements and transform CommonMask and     │
│ SubVectorsMask when ScalarTyNumElements != 1, mirroring the logic in the      │
│ instruction builder finalize.                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By adding the missing mask transformation in ShuffleCostEstimator::finalize   │
│ to handle REVEC cases, we ensure CommonMask and SubVectorsMask have           │
│ consistent sizes and semantics in the cost path, matching the emission path   │
│ behavior. This resolves the assertion failure and aligns cost estimation with │
│ instruction construction, preventing the SIGABRT during opt runs on the       │
│ provided reproducer.                                                          │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                               │
